<br>
The DW styles are:<br>
<br>
Twin Spikes - .07, Twin Return - .85, Shadows Edge - .64, Inflame .56, Orbit - .85, Eclipse - .86, Misty Gloom - .44, Obscure (detaunt) - .00, Penumbra - .88, Reflectional - .85,  Flank - .73, Dark Tendrils - .85, Shadow's Rain - .85, Dual Shadows - .87.<br>
<br>
Pole styles:<br>
<br>
Defenders Cross - .61, Deflect (detaunt) - .00, Defender's Faith - .36, Executioner - .90, Distract - .11, Crippling Blow - .43, Disabler - .68, Phalanx - .70, Mangle - .80, Defender's Rage - 1.19, Poleax - .65, Defender's Revenge - 1.00, Defender's Aegis - .92.<br>
<br>
Both lines have a couple of low level styles that suck badly, but they're low level and quickly outgrown. You might look at poles and say that Defender's Rage and Revenge are fantastic until you realize that although they're the highest damage in the game, they also require being styled on. NO ONE is stupid enough to style against a pole at least not after the first time. The Poleax style is so low it's totally worthless yet it's the 3rd highest pole style. Taking out the Rage/Revenge chain, all of the high level DW styles are better than the pole styles except for Defender's Aegis. Aegis is slightly higher damage than DS but it's also the 2nd in a rear positional chain.<br>
<br>
I really see no basis for your contention that Merc damage sucks. <br>
