<br>
Dual wielding isn't better than polearms (or any other 2Handed) in term of pure damage while styling. Only when pulse bladeturn is concerned or when out of endurance will dual wield do more damage.<br>
<br>
Style bonus is a multiplier *based* on your base dmg, the higher it is the more benefit you get from styles. So let's say your style is a 1.5x multiplier.<br>
<br>
if you do 100 base dmg., 100*1.5 = 150 dmg with style.<br>
add in offhand dmg (100) at 62% swing rate = 62 dmg<br>
total = 150+62 = 212 dmg<br>
<br>
while polearm gets 40% base dmg increase for being 2Handed.<br>
(100+40) * 1.5 = 210 dmg with style<br>
<br>
As you can see both do the same dmg. when styling if they have the same multiplier (derived from a similar growth rate).<br>
<br>
I have both a 50/50/30 polearmsman and merc. They don't really perform any different than each other in RvR. Polearms has better styles, albion 2H has even better styles, dual wield styles are not really important for a merc as they don't offer anything more than baseline styles, it's only for flurry and swinging your offhand more. <br>
<br>
And mythic will never give styled bonus for offhand weapons, they want to keep 2H/DW/CD etc damage close. It's been suggested since beta by players.<br>
